China Mobile, City Telecom, Huaneng: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-20T22:33:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/china-mobile-city-telecom-huaneng-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 1.6 percent to 23,896.10. The Hang
Seng China Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, gained 1.9 percent to 13,492.38.  China Mobile Ltd. (941)  (941 HK): The world’s biggest wireless
carrier by users said first-quarter net income rose 5.4 percent
to 26.9 billion yuan ($4.12 billion) from a year earlier. The
stock increased 0.8 percent to HK$72.60.  City Telecom (HK) Ltd. (1137 HK): The provider of fixed-
line phone services said net income for the six months ended Feb.
28 was HK$167.6 million ($21.6 million), compared with 116.4
million a year earlier. The stock advanced 1.4 percent to
HK$5.88.  Huaneng Power International Inc. (902)  (902 HK): The unit of
 China ’s biggest power producer said it will seek shareholders’
approval for proposals to sell short-term and super short-term
notes, and to issue yuan-denominated debt. The stock fell 4
percent to HK$4.37.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in  Tokyo  at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 